we can't do it alone.

00:03:03.220 --> 00:03:05.850
And that's why, today, we're
announcing the Google Photos

00:03:05.850 --> 00:03:08.640
partner program and
giving you, as developers,

00:03:08.640 --> 00:03:11.640
the tools and the
APIs you need to build

00:03:11.640 --> 00:03:16.510
amazing photo and video
experiences for your users.

00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:19.350
Now, as a developer, we know you
want to make your apps engaging

00:03:19.350 --> 00:03:20.760
and user friendly.

00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:23.040
And look, photos are a
great way to do that.

00:03:23.040 --> 00:03:25.830
But often, this involves
complex infrastructure

00:03:25.830 --> 00:03:29.130
for serving and having
to pay for storage just

00:03:29.130 --> 00:03:31.890
to duplicate the
user's own content.

00:03:31.890 --> 00:03:34.110
So we think that
should be easier, too.

00:03:34.110 --> 00:03:36.420
And so at the core of
the partner program

00:03:36.420 --> 00:03:40.590
is what we call the
Google Photos Library API.

00:03:40.590 --> 00:03:44.160
This makes available some of
our best technology to you

00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:47.820
to be able to bring the
best of Google Photos and AI

00:03:47.820 --> 00:03:50.550
to help solve real
problems for your users.

00:03:50.550 --> 00:03:52.630
And here's Ruchi
to tell you more.

00:03:52.630 --> 00:03:55.210
RUCHI BEZOLES: Thank you, Ben.

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:56.434
All right.

00:03:56.434 --> 00:03:57.850
Now, I'm going to
show you how you

00:03:57.850 --> 00:04:01.030
can use the API to build
more engaging experiences

00:04:01.030 --> 00:04:02.830
for your users.

00:04:02.830 --> 00:04:04.450
There are three
main functionalities

00:04:04.450 --> 00:04:06.490
that the API enables.

00:04:06.490 --> 00:04:09.070
The first is that it
will allow your users

00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:12.880
to access their library of
photos in your products.

00:04:12.880 --> 00:04:16.029
The second is that you will
be able to upload photos

00:04:16.029 --> 00:04:19.779
to a user's Google
Photos library.

00:04:19.779 --> 00:04:21.880
And third, it will
provide the infrastructure

00:04:21.880 --> 00:04:25.870
you need to enable sharing
of photos within your apps.

00:04:25.870 --> 00:04:27.700
It goes without
saying, but all of this

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:31.030
requires explicit user consent.

00:04:31.030 --> 00:04:33.220
So let's hone in on connect.

00:04:33.220 --> 00:04:36.115
One of the main things we wanted
to solve when building this API

00:04:36.115 --> 00:04:38.770
is to make it incredibly
simple for users

00:04:38.770 --> 00:04:42.460
to access and experience their
photos in their favorite apps

00:04:42.460 --> 00:04:46.090
and devices, many
of which you build.

00:04:46.090 --> 00:04:48.670
This could be in Timehop,
where once you've

00:04:48.670 --> 00:04:52.030
integrated your library and
given permission to use it,

00:04:52.030 --> 00:04:55.120
you'll get more personalized and
creative reminders of memories

00:04:55.120 --> 00:04:59.430
to look back on,
or on HP Sprocket.

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:01.330
It's a really cute,
portable printer

00:05:01.330 --> 00:05:03.840
that will let you print
photos from your own library

00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:05.260
as stickers on the go.

00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:10.070
While this functionality
is fantastic,

00:05:10.070 --> 00:05:13.730
to provide your users access to
their library in your products,

00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:16.510
we also want to help developers
surface the right photos

00:05:16.510 --> 00:05:19.080
a user might need in context.

00:05:19.080 --> 00:05:22.940
And you can do this thanks
to the filters functionality.

00:05:22.940 --> 00:05:27.290
There are four ways you can
filter a library of photos.

00:05:27.290 --> 00:05:30.290
The first is content
categories, and that's

00:05:30.290 --> 00:05:32.460
categories of photos
that a user has,

00:05:32.460 --> 00:05:35.630
whether it's pet photos,
selfies, landscape photos,

00:05:35.630 --> 00:05:38.180
landmark photos, so on.

00:05:38.180 --> 00:05:40.940
Then there's the date of
when the photos were created,

00:05:40.940 --> 00:05:44.370
so the time period
of photos and videos.

00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:45.530
And then there's the date--

00:05:45.530 --> 00:05:47.154
then there's the
media type, excuse me.

00:05:47.154 --> 00:05:49.760
So that's whether it's a photo
or a video or something else.

00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:51.840
You can pull those out, too.

00:05:51.840 --> 00:05:53.930
And finally, a
personal album a user

00:05:53.930 --> 00:05:58.070
already has created
in their account.

00:05:58.070 --> 00:05:59.010
OK.

