this information

00:13:15.900 --> 00:13:19.150
and bring it into a digital
album in Google Photos.

00:13:19.150 --> 00:13:24.390
So a scrapbook like what
you saw turned into this.

00:13:24.390 --> 00:13:28.320
So having hundreds of photos
in one place is really great,

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:31.230
but we also want to help users
find that exact photo they're

00:13:31.230 --> 00:13:33.630
talking about in a story.

00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:36.630
And thanks to the machine
intelligence in Google Photos,

00:13:36.630 --> 00:13:38.402
we can do that, too.

00:13:38.402 --> 00:13:40.110
So let's say I want
to show you my photos

00:13:40.110 --> 00:13:41.730
from the last few weeks.

00:13:41.730 --> 00:13:44.220
I'll just type in "me"
in the search bar,

00:13:44.220 --> 00:13:46.151
